  "edge_hypothesis": "VWAP_D is the volume-weighted average price — the institutional fair-value level where the most volume has transacted. It has NEVER been tested in any strategy despite being available since the indicator library was built. When price reclaims VWAP from below while stochastic is in the lower zone (below 40), it catches pullback entries at institutional value — mean-reversion anchored to actual traded volume rather than arbitrary time-based averages. This is fundamentally different from EMA-based pullbacks because VWAP weights by participation (volume), making it a natural magnet for institutional order flow. Stochastic in the lower zone (not extreme oversold) ensures we enter during pullbacks with room to run, not at exhaustion peaks. All ACCEPTs profit in ranging regimes — VWAP mean-reversion should be strongest in ranging markets where price oscillates around fair value.",
